WEBVTT

00:04.738 --> 00:07.707
<i>all: Ten, nine, eight,</i>

00:07.807 --> 00:09.542
<i>seven, six,</i>

00:09.642 --> 00:12.512
<i>five, four, three,</i>

00:12.579 --> 00:14.414
<i>two, one.</i>

00:14.514 --> 00:16.750
Happy New Year!

00:17.650 --> 00:19.219
<i>narrator: It had been</i>
<i>nearly four years</i>

00:19.319 --> 00:20.854
since the implosion
of his marriage,

00:20.920 --> 00:23.390
<i>and Marcus had spent</i>
<i>enough time drifting.</i>

00:23.490 --> 00:27.227
<i>Enough time wallowing.</i>
<i>Enough time fucking up.</i>

00:27.327 --> 00:28.928
<i>This was a new decade,</i>

00:29.029 --> 00:30.897
<i>and with it</i>
<i>came a fresh start.</i>

00:30.997 --> 00:33.099
<i>He had even waded</i>
<i>back into dating,</i>

00:33.199 --> 00:36.503
<i>proud of himself for simply</i>
<i>seeing where things took him.</i>

00:36.569 --> 00:38.671
- Yo, uh, wait,
who are you here with?

00:38.738 --> 00:40.206
- You now.

00:40.273 --> 00:42.042
<i>narrator: If Marcus</i>
<i>was sure of anything,</i>

00:42.108 --> 00:43.343
<i>he was sure of this:</i>

00:43.410 --> 00:46.346
<i>2020 was going to be his year.</i>

00:50.884 --> 00:54.788
<i>[light instrumental music]</i>

00:54.888 --> 00:56.222
- [sneezes]

00:59.025 --> 01:00.560
- [laughs]
[indistinct chatter]

01:00.627 --> 01:02.429
<i>narrator: Due to the state</i>
<i>of the world,</i>

01:02.529 --> 01:04.564
<i>what had started as simply</i>
<i>seeing where things took him</i>

01:04.631 --> 01:07.700
<i>had now resulted in Marcus</i>
<i>having a new roommate.</i>

01:07.767 --> 01:09.302
- Oh, my God.

01:09.402 --> 01:10.937
<i>narrator: And cohabitation</i>
<i>is often the true test</i>

01:11.037 --> 01:12.605
<i>of a bond between two people.</i>

01:12.705 --> 01:15.141
<i>- Marcus, sound good?</i>

01:15.241 --> 01:16.476
- Sounds good.

01:16.576 --> 01:18.378
<i>narrator: But sadly,</i>
<i>this was a test</i>

01:18.445 --> 01:21.081
<i>that he and Anjali</i>
<i>were quickly failing.</i>

01:21.147 --> 01:23.249
- Hey, baby, what's up?

01:23.316 --> 01:24.384
- Hey.

01:26.920 --> 01:29.122
Uh, where were you?

01:29.222 --> 01:31.424
- Sorry, I had to go
to a yoga class.

01:31.491 --> 01:34.661
- You had to go
to a yoga class?

01:34.761 --> 01:36.830
- Don't worry.
We were all super safe.

01:36.930 --> 01:39.432
Everyone had masks on.
We were six feet apart.

01:39.499 --> 01:40.834
Blah, blah, blah.

01:45.472 --> 01:46.906
- I--uh...

01:48.074 --> 01:50.443
Did you wash your hands?

01:51.344 --> 01:52.779
- What do you mean?

01:52.846 --> 01:55.281
- When you came in just now,
did you wash your hands?

01:56.416 --> 01:58.952
- Oh, I was totally
just about to.

02:02.322 --> 02:06.292
- And, uh, did you sanitize
this thing?

02:07.594 --> 02:10.196
- Like before I came back home?

02:10.296 --> 02:11.331
I think I did.

02:11.431 --> 02:14.367
- You-you think you did?

02:14.467 --> 02:16.703
- Yeah, someone
had sanitizer there.

02:17.770 --> 02:18.872
- Okay, uh, sorry.

02:18.972 --> 02:21.107
That's not making me
feel any better.

02:21.174 --> 02:23.309
- Yes, I sanitized it.

02:23.376 --> 02:25.211
I was so safe.

02:29.682 --> 02:31.451
- Okay, um...

02:33.286 --> 02:35.155
Look, Anjali,

02:35.221 --> 02:39.025
I don't think
this is working out.

02:39.125 --> 02:41.828
- Are you breaking up with me
because I went to a yoga class?

02:41.895 --> 02:43.530
- No, no, no,
not because of that.

02:43.630 --> 02:47.133
I mean, well, actually, yes,
but look...

02:47.200 --> 02:49.002
you're great.

02:49.068 --> 02:51.371
You're fun. I like you.

02:51.471 --> 02:53.706
It's--and I guess
that's just it.

02:53.806 --> 02:56.743
I-I just like you.

02:56.843 --> 02:58.011
And I gotta be honest here,

02:58.077 --> 02:59.812
I don't see this
going anywhere.

02:59.879 --> 03:01.748
So rather than
just floating along

03:01.848 --> 03:04.083
until we both hate each other,
I think we should call it.

03:04.184 --> 03:06.219
Plus, I'm not trying to die
over some yoga.

03:06.319 --> 03:08.855
- It was one class.
I won't go anymore.

03:08.922 --> 03:10.190
- Yeah, I, uh--

03:10.256 --> 03:11.858
[groaning]

03:13.760 --> 03:15.929
- Marcus, it's a pandemic.

03:17.997 --> 03:19.432
- I'm sorry, Anjali.

03:19.532 --> 03:22.502
<i>[sentimental music]</i>

03:22.569 --> 03:29.676
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:36.516 --> 03:38.551
[trumpet blasting]

03:38.618 --> 03:40.253
<i>narrator:</i>
<i>Marcus still believed</i>

03:40.353 --> 03:42.188
<i>that this would be his year</i>

03:42.255 --> 03:44.891
<i>despite the sudden</i>
<i>disappearance of his office,</i>

03:44.958 --> 03:47.560
<i>his gym, his new girlfriend,</i>

03:47.627 --> 03:48.962
<i>and his toilet paper.</i>

03:49.062 --> 03:50.797
<i>- Well, everyone knows that,</i>
<i>like,</i>

03:50.897 --> 03:52.765
<i>Zoom and Amazon and Netflix</i>
<i>are gonna be huge,</i>

03:52.865 --> 03:56.569
<i>but there's more value</i>
<i>in these less sexy companies.</i>

03:56.636 --> 03:58.571
<i>Write this down: Shot.</i>

03:58.638 --> 04:00.373
<i>Shot's gonna be a rocket ship.</i>

04:00.440 --> 04:02.475
- Okay, wait what's shot?

04:02.575 --> 04:04.644
<i>- Vials.</i>

04:04.744 --> 04:06.112
<i>Vaccines.</i>

04:06.212 --> 04:08.047
<i>No, dude there eventually</i>
<i>will be one.</i>

04:08.114 --> 04:10.984
<i>And we're going to need</i>
<i>hundreds of millions of vials.</i>

04:11.084 --> 04:13.119
<i>- Did you tell them</i>
<i>about the lumber?</i>

04:13.219 --> 04:15.421
<i>- Oh, my--lumber.</i>

04:15.488 --> 04:16.923
<i>Listen to me here.</i>

04:16.990 --> 04:18.891
<i>There is a company,</i>
<i>a lumber company,</i>

04:18.958 --> 04:21.327
<i>that I think is going to do</i>
<i>some sort of, like,</i>

04:21.427 --> 04:24.631
<i>outdoor dining setups for</i>
<i>the summer in New York City,</i>

04:24.731 --> 04:25.999
<i>should be huge.</i>

04:26.099 --> 04:27.634
- Are you sure you know
what you're doing?

04:27.734 --> 04:29.302
<i>- Listen, if you do</i>
<i>what I tell you</i>

04:29.402 --> 04:32.272
<i>when I tell you to,</i>
<i>you'll be fine.</i>

04:32.338 --> 04:33.973
- All right, bro.

04:34.073 --> 04:37.010
<i>[casual, bass-heavy music]</i>

04:37.110 --> 04:44.183
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:03.369 --> 05:05.004
- Whoa.
- Yeee...

05:05.104 --> 05:06.339
Hey, sis.

05:06.439 --> 05:08.675
- [laughs]
- Air hug. Air hug.

05:08.775 --> 05:10.510
- Hey.
- Smells good, Jaleesa.

05:10.610 --> 05:13.279
- Marcus, look,
I'm sorry we can't hug you.

05:13.346 --> 05:15.348
- Aw, nah, it's okay.

05:15.448 --> 05:16.983
- Ooh.
- [grunts]

05:18.017 --> 05:19.686
Here we go.

05:19.786 --> 05:21.187
[chuckles]

05:21.287 --> 05:24.290
That is a lot of toilet paper
for somebody that thought

05:24.357 --> 05:25.858
this was
gonna be over in two weeks.

05:25.958 --> 05:27.860
- I did. But don't be mad
at me and my baby

05:27.960 --> 05:30.396
'cause we have
a Costco membership, okay?

05:30.496 --> 05:31.864
And now, could you make sure

05:31.964 --> 05:34.300
you don't get, you know,
sweat on my floor?

05:34.367 --> 05:36.035
- I bike all the way
from Clinton Hill

05:36.135 --> 05:37.737
and you worried about sweat?

05:37.837 --> 05:40.173
- Yes 'cause it look like
you have a fever, it's scary.

05:40.239 --> 05:41.708
- Ooh!
- [laughs]

05:41.808 --> 05:43.343
Anyway, how you doing, bro?

05:43.409 --> 05:45.244
- Uh...

05:45.345 --> 05:46.979
I've been better.
I've been better.

05:47.046 --> 05:48.715
This--this pandemic
is tough solo.

05:48.815 --> 05:51.351
- Solo? What you mean, solo?
What happened to your girl?

05:51.417 --> 05:52.885
- Oh, we broke up.
- [gasps]

05:52.985 --> 05:55.188
- Damn, what happened?

05:55.254 --> 05:57.190
- [laughs] Well, I mean,
nothing happened.

05:57.256 --> 06:00.526
I just--I just wasn't
feeling it, so I ended it.

06:00.593 --> 06:02.695
- Oh, good for you.

06:02.762 --> 06:05.231
I-I-I didn't think
you had it in you.

06:05.331 --> 06:08.000
[laughter]

06:08.067 --> 06:10.436
- All right.
Well, how about you two?

06:10.536 --> 06:12.338
- We doing good.

06:12.405 --> 06:14.540
- We getting married.
- We getting married.

06:14.607 --> 06:16.342
- Ahh! Ahh!

06:16.409 --> 06:18.578
- August 20th.
We've got a date.

06:18.678 --> 06:20.413
- Oh, wait, wait, of this year?

06:20.513 --> 06:21.447
- Yeah.

06:21.547 --> 06:23.182
- Well, nobody's gonna come.

06:23.249 --> 06:25.251
- Perfect.
We'll save a fortune.

06:25.351 --> 06:27.387
[laughs]

06:27.453 --> 06:29.288
But you're gonna be
my best man, right?

06:32.024 --> 06:33.226
- Really?

06:33.292 --> 06:35.128
- Marcus, of course,
you're my brother.

06:35.228 --> 06:36.763
Who else would it be?

06:48.875 --> 06:50.276
- Hello?
<i>- Marcus.</i>

06:50.376 --> 06:52.779
<i>[coughs]</i>

06:52.879 --> 06:54.280
<i>How are you?</i>

06:55.214 --> 06:57.049
- I'm...okay.

06:57.116 --> 06:59.419
More importantly, how are you?

06:59.485 --> 07:00.753
<i>- I got the Rona.</i>

07:00.820 --> 07:02.255
- Dude, are you serious?

07:02.321 --> 07:04.957
<i>- This is no joke.</i>
<i>I'm hacking up a lung,</i>

07:05.057 --> 07:06.559
<i>I got a pounding headache.</i>

07:07.727 --> 07:09.162
<i>I can't taste shit.</i>
<i>[spits]</i>

07:09.262 --> 07:11.130
- Well, what are you doing
in the office?

07:11.230 --> 07:13.966
<i>- My wife kicked me out,</i>
<i>said it wasn't safe</i>

07:14.066 --> 07:16.269
<i>to be around the house</i>
<i>with the kids.</i>

07:16.335 --> 07:19.472
- Okay, well, just be sure
to take it easy.

07:19.572 --> 07:20.973
You look really sick, man.

07:21.073 --> 07:24.310
<i>- I wish I could,</i>
<i>but I got my hands full</i>

07:24.410 --> 07:26.512
<i>with all this</i>
<i>furlough business.</i>

07:26.612 --> 07:28.614
- Wait, what? Furlough?

07:28.681 --> 07:30.817
<i>- No, not you, buddy, okay?</i>
<i>Don't worry.</i>

07:30.917 --> 07:33.352
<i>That's why I'm calling.</i>
<i>I need you.</i>

07:33.453 --> 07:35.455
<i>It's only gonna be</i>
<i>five of us from now on.</i>

07:35.521 --> 07:37.657
<i>The Fab Five.</i>
- [sighs]

07:37.757 --> 07:39.859
<i>- At least I'm not</i>
<i>letting you go, you know?</i>

07:39.959 --> 07:41.761
<i>[coughs]</i>

07:44.030 --> 07:48.167
- Got it. Okay, well, thanks.
<i>- [coughing]</i>

07:48.267 --> 07:50.870
<i>All right, Marcus,</i>
<i>I'll talk to you later.</i>

07:51.938 --> 07:54.841
<i>[ambient music]</i>

07:54.941 --> 07:57.343
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:57.443 --> 07:58.611
- Yeah, uh, yeah, yeah.

07:58.678 --> 08:00.446
Yes, uh,
I just started working

08:00.513 --> 08:03.382
with Zelda, but I should be
able to get some new pages

08:03.483 --> 08:06.052
out of her
by the end of the month, so--

08:06.152 --> 08:08.387
<i>narrator: While friends of his</i>
<i>caught up on TV shows</i>

08:08.488 --> 08:09.889
<i>they'd been meaning to watch,</i>

08:09.989 --> 08:11.457
<i>and taught themselves</i>
<i>to bake bread,</i>

08:11.524 --> 08:13.826
<i>or roast whole chickens,</i>

08:13.893 --> 08:16.295
<i>Marcus suddenly found</i>
<i>himself overburdened</i>

08:16.362 --> 08:19.632
<i>with an obscene amount</i>
<i>of additional work.</i>

08:19.699 --> 08:24.203
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:24.303 --> 08:26.973
<i>But all of that</i>
<i>instantly felt small</i>

08:27.039 --> 08:30.009
<i>when he was once again</i>
<i>confronted by the pain</i>

08:30.076 --> 08:33.045
<i>and weight of the inhumanity</i>
<i>in the world.</i>

08:33.145 --> 08:34.247
<i>- Check his pulse!</i>

08:34.347 --> 08:35.581
<i>Check his pulse.</i>
<i>[indistinct]</i>

08:35.681 --> 08:36.983
<i>[crosstalk]</i>
<i>Check his pulse.</i>

08:37.049 --> 08:38.651
<i>Check his pulse, bro.</i>

08:38.718 --> 08:41.254
<i>Bro, check his pulse.</i>
<i>He coding, bro.</i>

08:41.354 --> 08:46.192
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:46.259 --> 08:47.927
[phone vibrates]

08:49.362 --> 08:52.331
<i>[music rises]</i>

08:52.398 --> 08:59.038
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:59.105 --> 09:02.208
[phone vibrating]

09:19.692 --> 09:20.860
- Hi.

09:20.927 --> 09:23.195
<i>- Hi.</i>

09:23.262 --> 09:24.430
<i>How are you?</i>

09:24.530 --> 09:26.432
- I'm not good.

09:26.532 --> 09:28.034
<i>- Me either.</i>

09:35.041 --> 09:36.876
- I didn't think
I'd hear from you again.

09:36.943 --> 09:38.978
<i>- I know, I shut you out,</i>

09:39.078 --> 09:40.780
<i>and I acted totally crazy.</i>

09:40.880 --> 09:42.214
- Yeah, you think?

09:42.281 --> 09:44.784
<i>- Can I--can I tell you</i>
<i>what happened?</i>

09:44.884 --> 09:46.319
- Uh...

09:48.654 --> 09:52.725
Okay.
<i>- Okay, I was in a dark place</i>

09:52.792 --> 09:54.961
<i>and I didn't know</i>
<i>what else to do.</i>

09:55.061 --> 09:56.462
<i>[sighs]</i>

09:56.562 --> 09:58.097
<i>When I went back to Maryland</i>
<i>to help my mom,</i>

09:58.164 --> 10:00.433
<i>I slept with the TaskRabbit</i>

10:00.499 --> 10:03.803
<i>who moved my dad's piano</i>
<i>into the storage unit, and--</i>

10:03.903 --> 10:05.271
- Are you fucking kidding me?

10:05.338 --> 10:07.139
<i>- I--I am so sorry.</i>

10:07.239 --> 10:09.308
<i>And I wanted to tell you</i>
<i>as soon as I came home,</i>

10:09.408 --> 10:10.977
<i>but I just--I couldn't.</i>

10:11.077 --> 10:13.012
- All right.

10:13.112 --> 10:14.814
[chuckles] All right.

10:19.518 --> 10:21.821
I mean, you know all that...

10:21.921 --> 10:24.991
really fucked me up, right?

10:25.091 --> 10:28.160
<i>- I'm so sorry.</i>

10:28.260 --> 10:30.863
- Like forget the fact
that you fucked a guy.

10:30.963 --> 10:37.136
How about the surprise birthday
party that I threw for you?

10:37.203 --> 10:38.638
Like an asshole.

10:38.704 --> 10:41.607
<i>- [sighs] Yeah.</i>

10:46.512 --> 10:48.381
- Did you, um...

10:51.283 --> 10:52.818
Did you ever get my voicemail?

10:52.885 --> 10:54.987
<i>- Yeah.</i>

10:55.054 --> 10:56.555
<i>That was--</i>
- Well, yeah,

10:56.656 --> 11:00.292
I'd eaten a shitload
of mushroom chocolates, so--

11:00.359 --> 11:03.863
<i>- Marcus, I'd love to see you</i>

11:03.963 --> 11:05.965
<i>so I can say sorry in person.</i>

11:11.804 --> 11:13.906
- Truthfully, Mia...

11:15.708 --> 11:17.043
I think I'm all set.

11:17.143 --> 11:20.212
I--I don't think...

11:20.312 --> 11:23.249
I can bear to hear more.

11:25.184 --> 11:26.719
<i>- Okay.</i>

11:28.254 --> 11:29.755
- Bye, Mia.

11:32.491 --> 11:33.893
[sighs]

11:43.102 --> 11:44.537
<i>- We're right behind</i>
<i>the police line.</i>

11:44.603 --> 11:45.905
<i>We're seeing now</i>
<i>more demonstrators</i>

11:46.005 --> 11:47.373
<i>come to the front.</i>

11:47.440 --> 11:49.075
<i>They seem like they're antsy,</i>
<i>Chris.</i>

11:49.175 --> 11:50.576
<i>They seem like</i>
<i>they're ready to charge.</i>

11:50.676 --> 11:52.344
[phone chiming]
<i>This is not a good look.</i>

11:52.411 --> 11:53.946
<i>This is not a good sign here</i>
<i>for these officers</i>

11:54.046 --> 11:55.514
<i>on the other side of it.</i>

11:55.581 --> 11:57.083
<i>And certainly not</i>
<i>for the demonstrators</i>

11:57.183 --> 11:59.885
<i>who are coming towards us.</i>

12:02.054 --> 12:04.924
- [sighs]

12:05.024 --> 12:06.459
<i>- When does--when does a--</i>

12:06.559 --> 12:07.760
<i>when does a protest</i>
<i>turn into a riot?</i>

12:07.860 --> 12:09.962
<i>- Exactly.</i>
- Hello?

12:11.630 --> 12:15.634
<i>- Marcus, buddy. How are you?</i>

12:15.735 --> 12:18.904
- Uh, hey, man.
I'm fine. Hanging in there.

12:18.971 --> 12:22.441
<i>- That's good. That's good.</i>

12:22.541 --> 12:24.043
<i>That video...</i>

12:27.279 --> 12:28.948
<i>It made me sick.</i>

12:29.048 --> 12:31.050
