<i>- I deleted my black square</i>

12:31.117 --> 12:33.319
<i>as soon as I realized</i>
<i>it was bad.</i>

12:34.386 --> 12:35.788
<i>But you're doing okay?</i>

12:35.888 --> 12:37.656
- I'm fine. Thanks.

12:37.757 --> 12:39.158
<i>- [clears throat]</i>

12:39.258 --> 12:40.726
<i>So obviously,</i>

12:40.793 --> 12:42.828
<i>Suttoncourt's gonna</i>
<i>put out a statement</i>

12:42.928 --> 12:45.631
<i>about all this,</i>
<i>and Marcus, of course,</i>

12:45.731 --> 12:47.266
<i>I wanted</i>
<i>to run it by you first.</i>

12:47.333 --> 12:51.637
- You wanted to run
Suttoncourt's statement by me?

12:51.737 --> 12:54.473
<i>- Well, I think it's important</i>

12:54.573 --> 12:58.944
<i>that we show solidarity</i>
<i>with the BLM movement.</i>

12:59.011 --> 13:00.946
- Okay, but why am I the one
that has to vet it?

13:01.013 --> 13:02.748
<i>- No, no, no, yeah,</i>
<i>I mean, you definitely--</i>

13:02.815 --> 13:05.117
<i>you don't have to do anything.</i>

13:05.184 --> 13:07.953
<i>I just--I wanted to give you</i>
<i>the opportunity.</i>

13:08.020 --> 13:11.357
- Oh, okay, so you want me
to sign off

13:11.457 --> 13:16.295
on your little corporate
PR statement

13:16.362 --> 13:20.633
after you fucking furloughed
everyone but us,

13:20.699 --> 13:24.336
and then dumped me
with all the work?

13:25.271 --> 13:28.207
<i>- Marcus,</i>
<i>the furlough is temporary.</i>

13:30.142 --> 13:31.677
<i>But what isn't temporary</i>

13:31.777 --> 13:34.513
<i>is our commitment</i>
<i>to understanding</i>

13:34.613 --> 13:37.116
<i>and supporting</i>
<i>the Black community.</i>

13:37.183 --> 13:38.851
- Are you reading
the fucking statement

13:38.951 --> 13:40.152
right now?

13:41.453 --> 13:43.556
<i>- Do you not like it?</i>
- No!

13:43.656 --> 13:44.990
No, I don't fucking like it.

13:45.057 --> 13:47.626
Are you--are you kidding me?

13:47.693 --> 13:49.295
[laughs]

13:51.797 --> 13:54.466
You do not support
the Black community.

13:56.302 --> 13:57.469
You don't.

13:57.536 --> 14:00.339
I bring you Black writers
with good,

14:00.406 --> 14:04.076
and I mean really good,
manuscripts,

14:04.176 --> 14:06.378
and automatically, man,
you're just like,

14:06.478 --> 14:09.081
"I don't get it,"
but what really sets me off

14:09.181 --> 14:11.217
is that I don't think

14:11.317 --> 14:14.320
you even actually care to.

14:14.386 --> 14:15.888
I brought you Trey Lang's book.

14:15.988 --> 14:17.923
I could barely get you
to read the fucking thing.

14:18.023 --> 14:20.860
But now, now, and this is
the whitest shit ever,

14:20.926 --> 14:24.396
now that it's a best-seller,
you have the poster

14:24.496 --> 14:25.998
hanging up
in your fucking office,

14:26.065 --> 14:30.202
and you have the gall
to ask me,

14:30.269 --> 14:33.239
the only Black dude
you kinda know,

14:33.339 --> 14:37.009
to rubber stamp your little
bullshit corporate PR statement

14:37.076 --> 14:39.612
so you look good?

14:39.712 --> 14:41.046
Bro!

14:45.184 --> 14:46.919
Hey, man, you know what?
Fuck Suttoncourt.

14:47.019 --> 14:51.190
Fuck all this--this
Johnny-come-lately bullshit,

14:51.257 --> 14:52.892
and Josh,

14:52.958 --> 14:54.960
fuck you too.

14:55.060 --> 14:57.129
Fuck you. I fucking quit.

14:59.131 --> 15:00.599
<i>- They're very deep going back</i>

15:00.699 --> 15:03.435
<i>towards central--</i>
<i>Centennial Olympic Park.</i>

15:03.535 --> 15:06.305
<i>I-I feel as though I just--</i>
<i>I believe I just heard</i>

15:06.405 --> 15:08.307
<i>what I--what I thought</i>
<i>was a taser deployed.</i>

15:08.407 --> 15:10.743
<i>I don't see anyone,</i>
<i>though, that is--</i>

15:10.809 --> 15:12.611
- [gasps]

15:35.734 --> 15:37.970
[sighs]

15:40.806 --> 15:43.142
<i>- You may now kiss your bride.</i>

15:44.476 --> 15:48.147
[applause]

15:48.247 --> 15:50.783
- Whoo! Whoo!

15:50.849 --> 15:52.151
- Whoo!

15:52.251 --> 15:55.321
[both laugh]

15:55.421 --> 15:58.490
<i>- I knew Jaleesa was the one.</i>

15:58.590 --> 16:00.092
- That's right.
Don't forget it.

16:00.159 --> 16:01.660
- Oh, never. Never, never.
- Mm-hmm.

16:03.262 --> 16:04.530
<i>[light music]</i>

16:04.630 --> 16:06.165
- Thank you so much
for coming.

16:06.265 --> 16:09.468
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:09.535 --> 16:11.337
- Yo.

16:11.437 --> 16:12.705
We doing the...

16:12.805 --> 16:15.674
- We might as well.
Bring it in.

16:15.774 --> 16:17.643
- I'm so happy for you, sis.

16:17.710 --> 16:19.812
Hey, congrats, Jaleesa.
This is crazy.

16:19.878 --> 16:20.813
- I know.
- I know.

16:20.879 --> 16:22.047
I used to hate this bitch.

16:22.147 --> 16:23.549
- Oh, don't you start.
[laughter]

16:23.649 --> 16:25.985
I'ma make a round.

16:26.051 --> 16:27.152
- Ooh.

16:27.219 --> 16:28.520
How 'bout that?
- How 'bout that?

16:28.620 --> 16:30.356
[both laugh]

16:30.456 --> 16:32.324
[sighs]

16:32.391 --> 16:34.226
Mom and Dad
are sad they missed this.

16:34.326 --> 16:35.361
- I know.

16:35.461 --> 16:36.695
I told 'em
they'll be my first stop

16:36.795 --> 16:38.364
once the vaccine come out.

16:38.464 --> 16:40.132
- Oh, you know, Dad's talking
about not getting it.

16:40.199 --> 16:41.867
- What is it about
old Black people?

16:41.967 --> 16:44.036
They make everything
a Tuskegee Experiment.

16:44.136 --> 16:45.537
- [laughs]
- That's your daddy.

16:45.637 --> 16:48.874
- But it was messed up though.
- It was. It was.

16:51.076 --> 16:54.046
- Damn, this is one
of the best days of my life.

16:54.146 --> 16:56.548
<i>[soft music]</i>

16:56.648 --> 16:59.318
I'm so happy for you, sis.

16:59.385 --> 17:00.519
- Oh.

17:00.586 --> 17:02.721
[sniffles, laughs]

17:02.821 --> 17:05.257
You're getting me
all teary-eyed.

17:05.357 --> 17:06.892
Let me get back to my girl.

17:06.992 --> 17:08.560
- All right.
- All right.

17:08.660 --> 17:10.863
<i>narrator: Having witnessed</i>
<i>his imperfect sister</i>

17:10.929 --> 17:13.532
<i>find happiness</i>
<i>in an imperfect world</i>

17:13.599 --> 17:16.068
<i>with an imperfect partner,</i>

17:16.168 --> 17:18.937
<i>Marcus's mind went back</i>
<i>to Mia.</i>

17:19.038 --> 17:26.111
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:27.179 --> 17:30.082
<i>[line trilling]</i>

17:30.182 --> 17:31.383
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:31.450 --> 17:33.886
<i>- Hello?</i>
- Hey, Mia.

17:33.952 --> 17:39.892
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:39.958 --> 17:41.760
- You really find out
who you are during a pandemic.

17:41.860 --> 17:44.530
I mean, I'm that bitch
that hoard N95s.

17:44.596 --> 17:45.764
I'll say it.
I don't give a shit.

17:45.864 --> 17:47.599
- I knew it!
- [laughs]

17:47.699 --> 17:50.102
- Old Billy Zane
in the "Titanic" ass

17:50.202 --> 17:51.904
just throwing old people
off the life raft.

17:51.970 --> 17:53.705
- Absolutely,
and without a doubt,

17:53.772 --> 17:55.107
you would have been
one of the first people

17:55.207 --> 17:56.408
I'd thrown off too.
- What?

17:56.475 --> 17:57.976
- I mean, no kids.

17:58.077 --> 18:00.212
No skills that I can think of.
Too skinny to eat.

18:00.279 --> 18:01.613
You're like one giant muscle.

18:01.713 --> 18:03.215
It's like, who wants that?
- Oh, okay.

18:03.282 --> 18:05.417
The muscle's where
the good meat is.

18:05.484 --> 18:06.952
- Is it though?
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

18:07.052 --> 18:08.487
Y'all could eat a fool
if y'all needed to.

18:08.587 --> 18:10.489
- [laughs]

18:15.127 --> 18:17.763
- So...uh...

18:20.232 --> 18:22.301
TaskRabbit.

18:23.602 --> 18:25.104
- I know.
[chuckles]

18:25.170 --> 18:26.338
I know.

18:30.576 --> 18:32.678
That whole thing, I--

18:38.951 --> 18:41.019
My mom's bipolar.

18:43.822 --> 18:45.991
And fuck, at the time,

18:46.091 --> 18:49.361
I was just--I really was
embarrassed about it.

18:49.461 --> 18:51.797
And then the shit with my dad
got so crazy,

18:51.864 --> 18:54.333
and, uh, I don't know,

18:54.433 --> 18:56.802
I just felt like...

18:56.869 --> 18:58.470
you were just seeing
all the bad stuff,

18:58.537 --> 19:00.706
and, um,

19:00.806 --> 19:02.875
I couldn't deal with it.

19:11.617 --> 19:14.653
- Thank you
for telling me that.

19:14.720 --> 19:16.021
- I mean,
don't be too impressed.

19:16.121 --> 19:19.691
That took, like,
ten months of therapy.

19:19.791 --> 19:22.561
And that shit was
all out of network.

19:26.498 --> 19:30.068
So thank you for listening.

19:30.169 --> 19:31.837
You didn't have to.

19:31.904 --> 19:34.840
<i>[soft music]</i>

19:34.907 --> 19:39.011
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:39.077 --> 19:40.212
I go this way.

19:40.312 --> 19:42.314
- Yeah. I'm...that way.

19:42.381 --> 19:44.216
- It was really nice
seeing you.

19:44.316 --> 19:47.252
- Yeah, it was good
to see you too.

19:48.854 --> 19:50.556
- See you, Marcus.

19:50.656 --> 19:52.224
- See you, Mia.

19:52.324 --> 19:59.398
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:11.677 --> 20:14.780
<i>[line trilling]</i>

20:16.248 --> 20:18.417
- [laughs]

20:18.517 --> 20:21.587
What, did I forget something?
- Yeah, um...

20:21.687 --> 20:24.089
Can you just come
back here for a sec?

20:24.189 --> 20:26.058
- You come over here.
- All right, fine.

20:26.124 --> 20:28.460
Look, why don't we just,
like, meet halfway?

20:28.560 --> 20:30.062
- [laughs]
Okay.

20:30.128 --> 20:31.263
- All right.

20:31.363 --> 20:37.102
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:37.202 --> 20:40.572
[sighs]
Okay. Uh...

20:40.639 --> 20:42.975
Look, man--fuck. Um...

20:45.377 --> 20:47.112
I just want you
to know something.

20:47.212 --> 20:48.447
All right?

20:48.547 --> 20:50.315
We've been through a lot.

20:50.415 --> 20:51.450
You know? Like, like, this...

20:51.550 --> 20:52.884
- Yeah.
- Whole thing.

20:52.951 --> 20:54.419
Yeah, it's been...
- Oh, it's intense.

20:54.486 --> 20:55.954
- It's been a fucking saga.
- Yeah, really.

20:56.054 --> 20:57.556
- And I just want
to let you know

20:57.623 --> 20:59.458
that I'm so proud of you, Mia,

20:59.558 --> 21:02.294
for going to therapy
and for working on yourself

21:02.394 --> 21:04.630
while dealing with all
this shit with your parents.

21:04.730 --> 21:07.499
And, I mean, like,
I can only imagine

21:07.599 --> 21:09.067
how that must have been.

21:09.134 --> 21:11.670
I know that you felt alone

21:11.770 --> 21:14.640
and that's why you blew shit up
the way that you did,

21:14.740 --> 21:15.974
but I just wish
you would have told me

21:16.074 --> 21:17.276
what was going on with you.

21:17.342 --> 21:18.810
I mean, not that
I could have fixed it.

21:18.910 --> 21:20.479
I couldn't have, I know that,
but I just--

21:20.579 --> 21:22.581
I just want
to be there for you.

21:23.949 --> 21:27.319
I always want
to be there for you.

21:27.419 --> 21:29.021
Even when you're being
an asshole,

21:29.121 --> 21:30.622
but I don't want you
to be anything

21:30.689 --> 21:33.825
other than what you are,
because that's who I love.

21:33.925 --> 21:35.794
- Okay.
That's a lot. This is a lot.

21:35.861 --> 21:37.796
- Yeah, I know. I know.

21:37.863 --> 21:40.799
<i>[Kim Jung Mi's "The Sun"]</i>

21:40.866 --> 21:44.303
<i>[soft acoustic music]</i>

21:44.369 --> 21:45.604
- Let's do it.

21:45.671 --> 21:52.778
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:55.447 --> 21:58.383
<i>- [singing in Korean]</i>

21:58.483 --> 22:05.557
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:39.925 --> 22:41.860
- You ready for some champagne?

22:41.927 --> 22:44.096
- It's only 9:00.

22:45.564 --> 22:47.265
You right. Fuck it.
Let's pop it.

22:47.366 --> 22:49.034
- That's what
I'm talking about.

22:49.101 --> 22:52.070
<i>narrator: Mia didn't seem</i>
<i>to be going anywhere.</i>

22:52.170 --> 22:53.705
<i>At least for now.</i>

22:53.772 --> 22:56.208
<i>Marcus was surprised to find</i>
<i>that he was willing</i>

22:56.274 --> 22:58.577
<i>to stand on the precipice</i>
<i>of risk,</i>

22:58.677 --> 23:01.012
<i>knowing that getting hurt</i>
<i>a second time by Mia</i>

23:01.079 --> 23:02.514
<i>would be devastating,</i>

23:02.581 --> 23:03.749
<i>but also knowing</i>

23:03.849 --> 23:06.952
<i>that not trying</i>
<i>would be worse.</i>

23:07.052 --> 23:08.587
- There you are.
- Thank you.

23:08.687 --> 23:10.188
God, I thought that I would

23:10.255 --> 23:13.125
want to see 2020 fucking end,

23:13.225 --> 23:15.127
but I don't think
I'm gonna make it.

23:15.227 --> 23:17.929
I'm tired.
- It'll end either way.

23:18.029 --> 23:19.898
- Not if we're in a time loop.

23:19.965 --> 23:21.633
[both laugh]

23:21.733 --> 23:23.468
- You need to go to sleep.

23:23.568 --> 23:26.238
- Do you think 2021's
gonna be any better?

23:27.873 --> 23:30.108
- It already is.

23:41.386 --> 23:44.456
<i>[cheering on TV]</i>

23:46.658 --> 23:49.761
<i>all: Ten, nine, eight,</i>

23:49.828 --> 23:53.932
<i>seven, six, five, four,</i>

23:53.999 --> 23:56.568
<i>three, two, one.</i>

23:56.635 --> 23:58.437
<i>Happy New Year!</i>

23:58.503 --> 24:01.807
<i>[cheers and applause]</i>

24:01.907 --> 24:04.810
<i>["Auld Lang Syne"]</i>
